&quot;November 12th, 1874: Price of sewing machine about half ways between Belleville &amp; Smithville. Barrett agreed to exchange machines and give a good one in place of the one left at my house. The next day was clear but cold.&quot;

&quot;13th: Fine day left Madoc in the morning &amp; walked to Queensboro. Took dinner at A.Diamonds R. Rayburn there he gave me Bills of Sundries sent to Murphys, Welshes &amp; Genarouxs Shantys. Rode from there to Linghams flats with Thos Lingham &amp; walked from there to Genarouxs Shanty where Lingham &amp; I staid over night. Borrowed a gun from L. Bisket.&quot;

&quot;Nover 14th 1874: Fine warm day sun shining. Left Genarouxs in the morning walked to Murphys Shanty distance about 10 miles. Called at Jas Mellons on the way. John Gartland &amp; Mellon repairing sleighs at Depot. Staid at Murphys Shanty all night. Shot a partridge on the Road&quot;

&quot;Sunday 15th 1874: Dark cloudy day snow on ground fell last night. I staid at Murphys wnt out with Murphy in theafter noon to look for Pine. Took the Gun along and shot four partridges.&quot;

Part of Denis Nealon's diary.
